1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:15,000
首先我要在此感謝朱牧師和譚牧師,我的老朋友,在此服侍大家。

2
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:31,000
It is with great joy to know that God is in our midst in spite of all our circumstances.

3
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:40,000
But we must learn to look at our circumstances correctly.

4
00:00:40,000 --> 00:00:47,000
In one of the art galleries in London, there is an entire floor dedicated to Renaissance art.

5
00:00:47,000 --> 00:01:14,000
The Italian masterpieces were there.One day there was a professor of art who went to visit this museum and look at the art pieces.

6
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:32,000
He is the professor of the history of art in Boston University.

7
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:53,000
The professor Robert Cummings came to this piece called "The Virgin and Child" by Lippi.

8
00:01:53,000 --> 00:02:11,000
Lippi is a 15th century Italian artist and the professor can see the masterpieces of the art stroke and the colors.

9
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:19,000
But somehow something is missing in this painting.

10
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:26,000
But he can't tell what is missing in this painting.

11
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:30,000
Suddenly the thought struck him.

12
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:44,000
What if this painting wasn't commissioned for an art gallery but in a prayer room?

13
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:59,000
And unlike a gallery where you stand to examine the art, in the prayer room you will be kneeling.

14
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:10,000
So professor Cummings did something he has never done before in a public gallery, he knelt before the art painting.

15
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:23,000
When he kneeled and looked up, everything is in perfect perspective and proportion.

16
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:35,000
The principle is our posture determines our perspective.

17
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:41,000
For things are not always what they seem.

18
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:46,000
Appearances can be deceiving.

19
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:54,000
The opposite of mere appearances is truth.

20
00:03:54,000 --> 00:04:10,000
Now there are two ways to view truth.The first is truth as content, propositions and principles.

21
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:16,000
The second is to look at truth as connection.

22
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:24,000
It is a connection to God and to reality.

23
00:04:24,000 --> 00:04:31,000
We must connect with reality.

24
00:04:31,000 --> 00:04:43,000
And we must see God in the reality of our life and experiences.

25
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:51,000
Because it will help us get our perspective correct.

26
00:04:51,000 --> 00:05:04,000
And one of the realities we must connect with is the reality of the wilderness experiences in our lives.

27
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:18,000
I want to talk to you about wilderness and warfare.Because all of us go through a spiritual wilderness.

28
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:27,000
It is represented by the dark and difficult circumstances of our lives.

29
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:35,000
But the Word of God tells us in Isaiah 40 verse 3, a voice cries out, "In the wilderness, prepare the way of the Lord."

30
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:40,000
上帝的說話在二塞亞書第四十章三節告訴我們,

31
00:05:40,000 --> 00:05:44,000
曠野裡有聲音說,預備耶和華的道路。

32
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:47,000
How do we prepare the way for the Lord?

33
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:49,000
我們如何預備耶和華的道路呢?

34
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:53,000
By preparing our hearts to look up to Him and trust Him.

35
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:57,000
預備耶和華的道路就是透過預備我們的心去看耶和華,去相信祂。

36
00:05:57,000 --> 00:06:00,000
You see, discipleship is not a mere program.

37
00:06:00,000 --> 00:06:03,000
門徒訓練不是一個程序。

38
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:06,000
Discipleship is a way of life.

39
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:09,000
門徒訓練是一個生活的方式。

40
00:06:09,000 --> 00:06:15,000
So everywhere in the world, I tell them the IDMC conference is not just how to do church.

41
00:06:15,000 --> 00:06:17,000
It's a way of life.

42
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:24,000
所以無論去到哪裏,我舉行這個約爾門訓練研習會,我都會告訴弟兄姊妹聽,

43
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:29,000
不是怎樣去搞教會,辦教會,而是一個生活方式。

44
00:06:29,000 --> 00:06:32,000
Because discipleship is a journey.

45
00:06:32,000 --> 00:06:35,000
因為門徒生活是一個旅程。

46
00:06:35,000 --> 00:06:38,000
And very often, this journey takes us through the wilderness.

47
00:06:38,000 --> 00:06:42,000
而這個旅程是一定會帶我們進入曠野。

48
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:47,000
When I visited Israel, there was a Christian tour guide who took us around.

49
00:06:47,000 --> 00:06:55,000
有一次我去巡遊聖地,一個基督徒的響導就帶著我們。

50
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:58,000
Then the bus passed through a wilderness.

51
00:06:58,000 --> 00:07:00,000
巴士就經過曠野。

52
00:07:00,000 --> 00:07:05,000
And the tour guide says, "Ah, the wilderness is a special place."

53
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:13,000
It's a place of emptiness, but it's a place where God speaks.

54
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:19,000
因為在這個地方裏面,上帝向人說話。

55
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:24,000
Because in the space of silence, God speaks.

56
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:28,000
在很靜的地方裏面,上帝向人說話。

57
00:07:28,000 --> 00:07:35,000
Blippically, the journey from Egypt to the Promised Land was through the wilderness.

58
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:41,000
在聖經裏面,由埃及去到英許之地中間是一個曠野。

59
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:44,000
So we ask the question, "Why the wilderness?"

60
00:07:44,000 --> 00:07:47,000
那我們就問個問題,為什麼要經過曠野呢?

61
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:53,000
In the Blippical narrative, the 12 spies were sent out to spy the land for 40 days.

62
00:07:53,000 --> 00:08:02,000
在聖經的技術裏面,以色列人就差遣了12個探子去觀察,了解這個英許之地。

63
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:07,000
Caleb and Joshua brought forth a report of faith, a good report.

64
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:17,000
約書亞和加納其中這兩個探子就是帶來憑著信心而有的一個好的報告。

65
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:23,000
Oh, but the other 10 spies gave a bad report because of doubt and unbelief.

66
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:29,000
其他那10個就因為他們不相信和懷疑,他們就給一個壞的報告。

67
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:33,000
The sad thing was the people of God did not believe Joshua and Caleb.

68
00:08:33,000 --> 00:08:36,000
They believed the 10 spies and they walked in their unbelief.

69
00:08:36,000 --> 00:08:48,000
很可悲的是,以色列人不聽加納和約書亞的報告,接受了那10個不信和懷疑的人的壞報告。

70
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:52,000
And the people cried out in fear and said, "We'd rather go back to Egypt."

71
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:57,000
那些以色列人就大聲說,我們寧願回去埃及。

72
00:08:57,000 --> 00:08:59,000
There were giants in the land.

73
00:08:59,000 --> 00:09:10,000
說那個英許之地下有巨人的。God told them for every day in the spying of the land, they will have one year in the wilderness.

74
00:09:10,000 --> 00:09:19,000
那上帝就和他們說,每一天他們來看這個英許之地,他們就要在曠野裡面留一年。

75
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:25,000
So for 40 days, because of their unbelief, they would spend 40 years in the wilderness.

76
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:32,000
因為他們不信,所以40天來去探索這個地,換來的就是他們40年要在曠野裡面。

77
00:09:32,000 --> 00:09:36,000
The question I ask is, why didn't God send them back to Egypt?

78
00:09:36,000 --> 00:09:38,000
Why send them into the wilderness?

79
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:44,000
那我們就問,為什麼上帝不差他們回去埃及,而是讓他們在曠野裡面呢?

80
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:48,000
When they were unbelieving, why didn't God say, "Poof, go back to Egypt."

81
00:09:48,000 --> 00:09:52,000
那他們都不信了,那就帶他們回去埃及。

82
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:57,000
There are two reasons, one is God's promise and the other is God's purpose.

83
00:09:57,000 --> 00:10:02,000
有兩個原因,一個就是上帝的承諾,另外一個就是上帝的目的。

84
00:10:02,000 --> 00:10:06,000
The first is because of God's promise to Abraham.

85
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:09,000
第一個原因就是上帝答應過阿巴拉罕。

86
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:12,000
God promised Abraham, your people will have a land.

87
00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:17,000
他答應阿巴拉罕,你的子民會有一個地方。

88
00:10:17,000 --> 00:10:22,000
They are passing through the wilderness to the promised land.

89
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:24,000
經過曠野,就會進入應許之地。

90
00:10:24,000 --> 00:10:30,000
If every time for their unbelief, God sends them back to Egypt, they will never get out of Egypt.

91
00:10:30,000 --> 00:10:36,000
如果每一次他們不相信,就送他們回去埃及,他們永遠都不會離開埃及。

92
00:10:36,000 --> 00:10:42,000
They will be delivered out of Egypt, walk around in unbelief, poof, they go back to Egypt.

93
00:10:42,000 --> 00:10:47,000
他們離開埃及,去到曠野,又不相信,又回到埃及。

94
00:10:47,000 --> 00:10:51,000
But God promised Abraham, they will have a promised land.

95
00:10:51,000 --> 00:10:55,000
因為上帝承諾過阿巴拉罕,他們有一個應許之地。

96
00:10:55,000 --> 00:11:00,000
The second reason why God didn't send them back to Egypt was because of God's purpose.

97
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:06,000
第二個原因,他們沒有回去埃及,因為上帝有這個目的。

98
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:11,000
God has a purpose for the wilderness to develop their faith.

99
00:11:11,000 --> 00:11:15,000
是要透過曠野去發展他們的信心。

100
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:21,000
So the wilderness wasn't just a place of punishment, it was a place of faith development.

101
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:28,000
所以曠野不單止是一個懲罰他們的地方,也是一個建立他們信心的地方。

102
00:11:28,000 --> 00:11:32,000
It was in the wilderness that faith was being sanctified.

103
00:11:32,000 --> 00:11:36,000
是在這個曠野裏面,他們的信心得到聖化。

104
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:44,000
You see, salvation is God getting us out of the world, but sanctification, God is getting the world out of us.

105
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:54,000
救贖就是上帝帶我們離開這個世界,而聖化就是將世界從我們的生命裏面拿走。

106
00:11:54,000 --> 00:11:58,000
So the wilderness is not a destination, it's a transit point.

107
00:11:58,000 --> 00:12:03,000
所以曠野並不是一個目的地,曠野只不過是一個中途站而已。

108
00:12:03,000 --> 00:12:08,000
In other words, God leads us to the wilderness, He will lead us through the wilderness.

109
00:12:08,000 --> 00:12:14,000
所以上帝並不是帶我們去曠野,而是經過曠野。

110
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:20,000
Please understand, God doesn't want us to live in the wilderness, He wants us to learn from the wilderness.

111
00:12:20,000 --> 00:12:27,000
所以上帝並不是要我們活在曠野裏面,上帝是要我們在曠野裏面有所學習。

112
00:12:27,000 --> 00:12:31,000
But there is good news and there is bad news in the wilderness.

113
00:12:31,000 --> 00:12:35,000
所以在曠野裏面有壞消息亦都有好消息。

114
00:12:35,000 --> 00:12:38,000
Let me first explore the bad news with you.

115
00:12:38,000 --> 00:12:40,000
先講壞消息。

116
00:12:40,000 --> 00:12:43,000
The bad news is that we can lose our bearing in the wilderness.

117
00:12:43,000 --> 00:12:47,000
第一個壞消息就是在曠野裏面我們可以迷失方向。

118
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:50,000
We can get confused and lost in the wilderness.

119
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:55,000
我們在曠野裏面因為好混亂,所以我們就不知道去哪裏。

120
00:12:55,000 --> 00:13:00,000
Because the wilderness is a place of confusion and desperation.

121
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:04,000
曠野就是混亂及很淒慘的地方。

122
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:08,000
And in the wilderness, it's easy to get lost.

123
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:11,000
在曠野裏面真的很容易迷路。

124
00:13:11,000 --> 00:13:13,000
We don't know what direction to take.

125
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:16,000
我們都不知道究竟哪一個方向才是對的。

126
00:13:16,000 --> 00:13:19,000
The circumstances confuse us.

127
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:21,000
各個環境令我們混亂。

128
00:13:21,000 --> 00:13:25,000
We ask the question, why me? Why this? Why now?

129
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:31,000
我們就問這個問題,為什麼是這樣的?為什麼現在是這樣的?為什麼我是這樣的呢?

130
00:13:31,000 --> 00:13:34,000
I was once lost in Africa.

131
00:13:34,000 --> 00:13:36,000
有一次我從非洲迷路。

132
00:13:36,000 --> 00:13:41,000
I was going up from the southern part to Johannesburg.

133
00:13:41,000 --> 00:13:48,000
有一次我從非洲的南邊回到約翰尼斯堡。

134
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:53,000
And I didn't realize that when winter comes, the sun sets very early.

135
00:13:53,000 --> 00:14:01,000
我又不是很了解到冬季的太陽落山落得很快。

136
00:14:01,000 --> 00:14:07,000
So suddenly, I found myself in the late afternoon driving in the darkness.

137
00:14:07,000 --> 00:14:11,000
很快,本來還沒到黃昏就已經黑了。

138
00:14:11,000 --> 00:14:15,000
I look in the rear view mirror, everything is dark.

139
00:14:15,000 --> 00:14:18,000
In front of the lamp, there is no cars around.

140
00:14:18,000 --> 00:14:24,000
我望到後鏡,後面是黑漆漆的,前面也是黑漆漆的。

141
00:14:24,000 --> 00:14:27,000
There is no road lights, there is no road sign.

142
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:30,000
沒有街燈,也沒有路標。

143
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:34,000
Only four of us in the car, my wife, myself and the missionary couple behind.

144
00:14:34,000 --> 00:14:39,000
我們現在的車裡面四個人,我和我太太,後面的就是孫教士夫婦。

145
00:14:39,000 --> 00:14:43,000
We were completely lost in the wilderness.

146
00:14:43,000 --> 00:14:45,000
我們真的是絕對迷路。

147
00:14:45,000 --> 00:14:51,000
And miles and miles as I drive along, I am not sure am I in the right direction in the darkness.

148
00:14:51,000 --> 00:14:56,000
一路這樣駛下去,我都不知道究竟我行駛的方向是否正確。

149
00:14:56,000 --> 00:15:02,000
There was no cars around, just one solitary car for miles and miles and miles in the darkness.

150
00:15:02,000 --> 00:15:07,000
周圍都沒有車,只是我們一輛車,然後我一路這樣駛下去,都是黑漆漆的。

151
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:11,000
I was driving on hoping for some road signs, but there was none.

152
00:15:11,000 --> 00:15:16,000
我一路行的時候,我一路等著看看有沒有路牌,但是原來沒有的。

153
00:15:16,000 --> 00:15:18,000
If you were me, what would you do?

154
00:15:18,000 --> 00:15:19,000
如果你是我,你會怎樣?

155
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:25,000
There is no GPS, there is no signal, everything is just vastness and lostness.

156
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:30,000
沒有導航,也沒有訊號,就是一片黑漆漆。

157
00:15:30,000 --> 00:15:32,000
I finally have to stop the car.

158
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:34,000
最後我就停了車。

159
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:36,000
And I look up at the night sky.

160
00:15:36,000 --> 00:15:40,000
我然後望著晚上的星空。

161
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:43,000
I was looking at the stars to find a sense of direction.

162
00:15:43,000 --> 00:15:47,000
我望上面的星星,我嘗試去找一些方向。

163
00:15:47,000 --> 00:15:49,000
I found the Southern Cross.

164
00:15:49,000 --> 00:15:51,000
我就找到南方的十字架。

165
00:15:51,000 --> 00:15:54,000
And from the Southern Cross, the opposite is towards the North.

166
00:15:54,000 --> 00:15:58,000
南方的十字架的相反方向就是北。

167
00:15:58,000 --> 00:16:03,000
So I found where the North is, and I drove towards the North and found Johannesburg.

168
00:16:03,000 --> 00:16:07,000
我就向著北方繼續這樣駛,結果我就找到約翰尼斯堡。

169
00:16:07,000 --> 00:16:11,000
That day, I learned an important spiritual lesson.

170
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:13,000
那一天,我學到一個屬靈的功課。

171
00:16:13,000 --> 00:16:16,000
When you are lost, look up.

172
00:16:16,000 --> 00:16:19,000
你迷失了方向,你就要向上望。

173
00:16:19,000 --> 00:16:23,000
In the wilderness, prepare the way for the Lord. Look up.

174
00:16:23,000 --> 00:16:29,000
在曠野裏面,你要預備夜禍的道路,就是你要望上面。

175
00:16:29,000 --> 00:16:32,000
Because it's easy to lose our bearings in the wilderness.

176
00:16:32,000 --> 00:16:36,000
因為在曠野裏面,很容易就迷失了方向。

177
00:16:36,000 --> 00:16:40,000
The second news, we can lose our confidence in the wilderness.

178
00:16:40,000 --> 00:16:46,000
第二個壞消息就是,我們在曠野裏面很容易就失去了把握,失去了信心。

179
00:16:46,000 --> 00:16:50,000
Because when we lose our bearings, we get disoriented.

180
00:16:50,000 --> 00:16:54,000
因為我們失去了方向,我們就不知道究竟現在在哪裏。

181
00:16:54,000 --> 00:16:58,000
And because we don't know how to proceed, we lose our sense of confidence.

182
00:16:58,000 --> 00:17:02,000
當我們都不知道下一步是怎樣的時候,我們就失去了把握。

183
00:17:02,000 --> 00:17:06,000
The third bad news is that when I drove on and on, my confidence became less and less.

184
00:17:06,000 --> 00:17:11,000
就是好像在非洲那裏,一路駕駛就越來越沒有把握。

185
00:17:11,000 --> 00:17:17,000
The third bad news is that as we lose our bearing and confidence, we tend to wander in the wilderness.

186
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:26,000
而第三個壞消息就是,我們失去了方向,又失去了信心,把握的時候,我們就開始在那裏轉圈轉圈。

187
00:17:26,000 --> 00:17:30,000
Because the wilderness can be complex and confusing.

188
00:17:30,000 --> 00:17:35,000
因為曠野真的很複雜,令人很混亂。

189
00:17:35,000 --> 00:17:41,000
In our life, the difficult circumstances can be complex and confusing.

190
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:47,000
在我們的生命裏面,有很多事情是很複雜,令我們很混亂。

191
00:17:47,000 --> 00:17:50,000
Some have lost their job or they are retrenched.

192
00:17:50,000 --> 00:17:55,000
有一些人沒有了工作,結果就困在那裏。

193
00:17:55,000 --> 00:17:58,000
Some face financial crisis or health concerns.

194
00:17:58,000 --> 00:18:02,000
有些人面對經濟的問題,有些人面對健康的問題。

195
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:06,000
Some have family problems, marriage problems or children problems.

196
00:18:06,000 --> 00:18:12,000
有一些人面對家庭關係的問題,婚姻的問題和兒女的問題。

197
00:18:12,000 --> 00:18:17,000
There are all kinds of things that come at us in our wilderness.

198
00:18:17,000 --> 00:18:21,000
在曠野裏面,不同的東西就湧過來。

199
00:18:21,000 --> 00:18:26,000
And the scary thing is we can lose our sense of perspective.

200
00:18:26,000 --> 00:18:32,000
令人驚懼的就是我們很容易失去了正確的視野。

201
00:18:32,000 --> 00:18:36,000
And as a result, the four bad news is wilderness wondering where is us.

202
00:18:36,000 --> 00:18:43,000
第四個壞的消息就是曠野令我們疲乏不堪。

203
00:18:43,000 --> 00:18:47,000
We don't quite understand what is happening and why.

204
00:18:47,000 --> 00:18:51,000
我們不知道究竟發生了什麼和為了什麼發生。

205
00:18:51,000 --> 00:18:58,000
We are trying to make sense of what is happening in our circumstances and we get more confused or more discouraged.

206
00:18:58,000 --> 00:19:03,000
越是想了解什麼發生,我們就越是混亂,我們就越是沮喪。

207
00:19:03,000 --> 00:19:07,000
And the fifth bad news is the wilderness is a battleground.

208
00:19:07,000 --> 00:19:11,000
第五個壞消息就是這個曠野其實是一個戰場。

209
00:19:11,000 --> 00:19:14,000
Not many know the wilderness is not a playground.

210
00:19:14,000 --> 00:19:23,000
每個人都知道曠野不是遊樂場。但是我們很多時候忘記曠野其實是一個戰場。

211
00:19:23,000 --> 00:19:30,000
Because Satan leverages the wilderness to confuse and create doubt in our soul.

212
00:19:30,000 --> 00:19:40,000
因為撒旦是利用這個曠野來製造懷疑和不順。

213
00:19:40,000 --> 00:19:44,000
And our wilderness become a battleground, but it's a different kind of battleground.

214
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:47,000
曠野是一個戰場,但是是一個另類的戰場。

215
00:19:47,000 --> 00:19:50,000
Because there are no armies or chariots on the outside.

216
00:19:50,000 --> 00:19:53,000
因為外面你看不到坦克車和火炮。

217
00:19:53,000 --> 00:19:55,000
The battle is within.

218
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:57,000
這個戰場在裏面。

219
00:19:57,000 --> 00:20:01,000
The battle is our doubts and our fears, our anxieties.

220
00:20:01,000 --> 00:20:06,000
這個是我們內心的恐懼、焦慮、不安。

221
00:20:06,000 --> 00:20:10,000
The inner battle that has become a war zone inside.

222
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:14,000
這個是裏面那個戰場令到我們很辛苦。

223
00:20:14,000 --> 00:20:18,000
And our foundation for our faith from the Word of God is shifted.

224
00:20:18,000 --> 00:20:25,000
我們信心的基礎就會進入,我們的根基就會進入詭辯。

225
00:20:25,000 --> 00:20:30,000
Let me share with you what I found to be the greatest problem in discipleship today.

226
00:20:30,000 --> 00:20:35,000
讓我和大家分享,今天門徒的生活最大的挑戰是什麼?

227
00:20:35,000 --> 00:20:39,000
The biggest challenge is we shift our foundation from the Word of God.

228
00:20:39,000 --> 00:20:44,000
今天最大的挑戰就是我們轉移我們信仰的基礎,離開上帝的說話。

229
00:20:44,000 --> 00:20:47,000
That doesn't just mean we don't know God's Word.

230
00:20:47,000 --> 00:20:50,000
不是說我們不認識上帝的說話。

231
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:52,000
We know the Word of God is important.

232
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:53,000
我們知道上帝的說話重要。

233
00:20:53,000 --> 00:20:55,000
We know it should be the foundation of our faith.

234
00:20:55,000 --> 00:20:58,000
我們知道上帝的說話是我們信仰的基礎。

235
00:20:58,000 --> 00:21:02,000
So we must have a theological anchor and a biblical foundation.

236
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:09,000
我們需要一個神學的基礎,和我們按照聖經的鬧。

237
00:21:09,000 --> 00:21:12,000
And the Bible will give us a sound biblical worldview.

238
00:21:12,000 --> 00:21:18,000
上帝的說話,這個聖經就給我們一個合乎聖經的世界觀。

239
00:21:18,000 --> 00:21:23,000
To understand God and His unchanging purposes by which He works in our life.

240
00:21:23,000 --> 00:21:28,000
如此我們就明白上帝的意思,上帝的計劃,和在我們生命裡面的計劃。

241
00:21:28,000 --> 00:21:31,000
To have a meaningful understanding of the world and how to live in it.

242
00:21:31,000 --> 00:21:37,000
也都是了解這個世界很清楚的,知道我們應該如何在這個世界裡面生活。

243
00:21:37,000 --> 00:21:42,000
So we know the Bible is truth and it should be the foundation of our life.

244
00:21:42,000 --> 00:21:47,000
所以我們知道的聖經是真理,是我們生命的盤石。

245
00:21:47,000 --> 00:21:48,000
But here comes the problem.

246
00:21:48,000 --> 00:21:49,000
但問題來了。

247
00:21:49,000 --> 00:21:52,000
We enter into a season of wilderness.

248
00:21:52,000 --> 00:21:55,000
當我們進入曠野的季節。

249
00:21:55,000 --> 00:21:56,000
It disorientates us.

250
00:21:56,000 --> 00:21:58,000
令到我們亂了路。

251
00:21:58,000 --> 00:22:03,000
Dogs come into our minds and anxieties and worries come to our hearts.

252
00:22:03,000 --> 00:22:08,000
懷疑、憂慮各樣的困惑進入我們的生命。

253
00:22:08,000 --> 00:22:10,000
It impacts our feelings and our emotions.

254
00:22:10,000 --> 00:22:14,000
衝擊我們的感覺和情緒。

255
00:22:14,000 --> 00:22:18,000
And out of our insecurity and feelings, we make our choices.

256
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:24,000
出於我們的感覺和不安,我們就作出一些選擇。

257
00:22:24,000 --> 00:22:29,000
Our choices based upon our feelings will bring forth our behavior.

258
00:22:29,000 --> 00:22:35,000
當日出於這些感覺、情緒而帶來的我們的選擇就帶來一些行為。

259
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:41,000
But because it's based upon our feelings, not upon faith, we are deviated from the Word of God.

260
00:22:41,000 --> 00:22:46,000
因為我們所作出的這些選擇是出於我們的感覺而不是出於上帝的說話。

261
00:22:46,000 --> 00:22:50,000
We become like the children of Israel in the wilderness.

262
00:22:50,000 --> 00:22:52,000
They walk in unbelief.

263
00:22:52,000 --> 00:22:59,000
我們就好像以色列的子民那樣,他們在生活裏面也活出他們的不信。

264
00:22:59,000 --> 00:23:04,000
Now we have two operating systems, two core belief systems within us.

265
00:23:04,000 --> 00:23:09,000
那現在我們的生命裏面就有兩個核心的信仰系統了。

266
00:23:09,000 --> 00:23:11,000
We have the Word of God that we say is true.

267
00:23:11,000 --> 00:23:14,000
我們有一個就是上帝的說話我們知道是真理。

268
00:23:14,000 --> 00:23:19,000
But we have our own values that is formed by our own behavior based upon our feelings.

269
00:23:19,000 --> 00:23:25,000
那有另外一個就是出於我們的情緒感覺而引伸出來的行動這個系統了。

270
00:23:25,000 --> 00:23:29,000
We are to walk in faith, but we are also walking in unbelief and doubt.

271
00:23:29,000 --> 00:23:38,000
我們應該是憑信念去生活,但是實際上我們就在我們的猶疑裏面進入另外一個生命生活。

272
00:23:38,000 --> 00:23:43,000
We ought to trust God fully in faith, but we are not trusting Him fully because of our doubts.

273
00:23:43,000 --> 00:23:49,000
我們應該是存然的信靠上帝,不過因為我們的懷疑,我們就不是很順了。

274
00:23:49,000 --> 00:23:55,000
Now no computer system can work on two operating systems within one computer.

275
00:23:55,000 --> 00:24:01,000
你都知道的,沒有一個電腦可以同時有兩個操作系統運行的。

276
00:24:01,000 --> 00:24:06,000
So within the human soul, we cannot operate by two core belief systems.

277
00:24:06,000 --> 00:24:10,000
所以我們的靈魂都不能夠同時有兩個操作系統的。

278
00:24:10,000 --> 00:24:11,000
Now we have a problem.

279
00:24:11,000 --> 00:24:13,000
我們又找問題了。

280
00:24:13,000 --> 00:24:19,000
What do we do when we have the Word of God, but at the same time the wisdom of the world and the things of the world?

281
00:24:19,000 --> 00:24:25,000
現在我們又有神的說話,然後又有世界的想法和智慧。

282
00:24:25,000 --> 00:24:27,000
We have three choices.

283
00:24:27,000 --> 00:24:29,000
我們有三個選擇。

284
00:24:29,000 --> 00:24:35,000
The first is repentance. We turn from the world and our own feelings and we walk by faith in the Word of God.

285
00:24:35,000 --> 00:24:42,000
所以就是悔改,轉離我們的感覺引發的那些選擇,然後歸回上帝的說話。

286
00:24:42,000 --> 00:24:47,000
Second choice, we backslide and we turn away from God and we live our own way.

287
00:24:47,000 --> 00:24:57,000
第二個選擇就是我們決定背棄我們的信仰,離開上帝的說話,跟著我們的感受去生活。

288
00:24:57,000 --> 00:25:03,000
But the problem in the global church is many Christians choose the third choice.

289
00:25:03,000 --> 00:25:09,000
很可惜的是全球的教會的弟兄姊妹作出第三個選擇。

290
00:25:09,000 --> 00:25:14,000
They continue to live with two opposing value systems within one soul.

291
00:25:14,000 --> 00:25:22,000
他們繼續容許這個不同的相反矛盾的系統在他們的靈魂裏面作祟。

292
00:25:22,000 --> 00:25:27,000
But I just told you that the human soul cannot accommodate the two belief systems.

293
00:25:27,000 --> 00:25:32,000
我剛剛才告訴大家,人的靈魂不能夠兩個系統同時操作。

294
00:25:32,000 --> 00:25:38,000
So how do we make the third choice? How can many Christians choose to have these two within them?

295
00:25:38,000 --> 00:25:43,000
那些人怎樣去做出第三個選擇呢?

296
00:25:43,000 --> 00:25:49,000
Because they give lip service to the word of God and live however they choose.

297
00:25:49,000 --> 00:25:59,000
他們的口就是跟著上帝的說話,不過他們的心就是照著他們的感覺,這個世界所給他們的智慧來的。

298
00:25:59,000 --> 00:26:02,000
On Sunday, we come to church to worship God.

299
00:26:02,000 --> 00:26:05,000
星期一來到這個地方去敬拜上帝。

300
00:26:05,000 --> 00:26:07,000
There is one belief system in the word.

301
00:26:07,000 --> 00:26:09,000
這一個就是信靠上帝的說話。

302
00:26:09,000 --> 00:26:14,000
In the cell group, we study the scriptures that we use Christian language.

303
00:26:14,000 --> 00:26:17,000
在細胞小組裏面,團契裏面,我們就用聖經的說話。

304
00:26:17,000 --> 00:26:20,000
這一個是基督教的言語。

305
00:26:20,000 --> 00:26:24,000
But this lip service,這些是咀唇的敬拜。

306
00:26:24,000 --> 00:26:30,000
Because from Monday and every day of the week, we live according to our own worldly value system.

307
00:26:30,000 --> 00:26:39,000
只是在聚會的時間才出現的,其他的時候,我們就是照著這個世界的價值觀念、信念去做。

308
00:26:39,000 --> 00:26:43,000
When that happens, the wilderness is a battleground of two systems.

309
00:26:43,000 --> 00:26:49,000
當這個情況出現的時候,曠野就成為這兩個系統的戰場。

310
00:26:49,000 --> 00:26:52,000
Life in the flesh or life in the spirit.

311
00:26:52,000 --> 00:26:59,000
在肉體的生活,或者是在聖靈的生活。

312
00:26:59,000 --> 00:27:03,000
Grounded in the value system of the word of God or the world.

313
00:27:03,000 --> 00:27:08,000
用聖經上帝的說話來作為我們的信念的根基,

314
00:27:08,000 --> 00:27:11,000
還是這個世界的價值作為我們信念的根基。

315
00:27:11,000 --> 00:27:15,000
And in that struggle, we are really lost in the wilderness.

316
00:27:15,000 --> 00:27:22,000
當我們是這樣容許這個戰場出現的時候,我們就真的迷失了。

317
00:27:22,000 --> 00:27:27,000
But God wants to use the wilderness to strengthen our faith.

318
00:27:27,000 --> 00:27:32,000
但是上帝是要用曠野來兼顧我們的信仰的。

319
00:27:32,000 --> 00:27:37,000
Provided we are willing to prepare the way of the Lord in the wilderness.

320
00:27:37,000 --> 00:27:44,000
但是有一個條件就是我們要願意預備上帝的道路。

321
00:27:44,000 --> 00:27:49,000
And when we prepare the way of God in the wilderness, there is good news in the wilderness.

322
00:27:49,000 --> 00:27:55,000
當我們願意預備上帝的道路,在曠野裡預備的時候,我們就有一個好消息。

323
00:27:55,000 --> 00:27:59,000
The first good news is that we can experience God's presence in the wilderness.

324
00:27:59,000 --> 00:28:04,000
第一個好消息就是在曠野裡,我們可以經歷上帝同在。

325
00:28:04,000 --> 00:28:07,000
That even in the wilderness, there are seasons of refreshing.

326
00:28:07,000 --> 00:28:16,000
雖然在曠野裡這麼淒慘,我們仍然可以很新鮮地經歷生命。

327
00:28:16,000 --> 00:28:23,000
Just like in the biblical times, there was a pillar of cloud by day and a pillar of fire by night to guide them in the presence of God.

328
00:28:23,000 --> 00:28:34,000
就好像在聖經的日子裡,上帝的臨在在日間的雲柱,夜間的火柱裡,去引導著以色列人。

329
00:28:34,000 --> 00:28:38,000
And when we trust God in the wilderness, the presence of God is there.

330
00:28:38,000 --> 00:28:42,000
當我們信上帝的時候,上帝的臨在就會顯然。

331
00:28:42,000 --> 00:28:46,000
The second good news is we can receive God's provision in the wilderness.

332
00:28:46,000 --> 00:28:50,000
第二個好消息就是在曠野裡,我們可以得著上帝的供應。

333
00:28:50,000 --> 00:28:55,000
Just like God provided for the children of Israel in the wilderness for 40 years.

334
00:28:55,000 --> 00:29:04,000
就好像耶和華上帝在曠野裡供應以色列的子民40年這麼久。

335
00:29:04,000 --> 00:29:07,000
When there is no water, God provided them water from the rock.

336
00:29:07,000 --> 00:29:11,000
沒有水的時候,上帝就在石頭裡供應他們水源。

337
00:29:11,000 --> 00:29:15,000
When there is no food, God provided for them manna from heaven.

338
00:29:15,000 --> 00:29:19,000
沒有食物,上帝從天降下晚拿給他們。

339
00:29:19,000 --> 00:29:24,000
In the wilderness, when we look to God and trust Him, He provides for us.

340
00:29:24,000 --> 00:29:29,000
當我們在曠野裡,我們向上仰望,上帝就供應我們。

341
00:29:29,000 --> 00:29:33,000
For God will never lead us when His grace cannot keep us.

342
00:29:33,000 --> 00:29:38,000
因為上帝永遠不會帶我們去一個地方,祂不能保護我們。

343
00:29:38,000 --> 00:29:43,000
The third good news is we can witness God's power in the wilderness.

344
00:29:43,000 --> 00:29:47,000
第三個好消息就是在曠野裡,我們可以經歷上帝的能力。

345
00:29:47,000 --> 00:29:51,000
God shows us His power when we trust Him.

346
00:29:51,000 --> 00:29:54,000
當我們相信祂的時候,上帝就顯示祂的能力。

347
00:29:54,000 --> 00:30:01,000
God shows us His power when we see His work miraculously in and through our lives.

348
00:30:01,000 --> 00:30:07,000
當我們相信祂的時候,上帝就將祂的能力在我們的生命裡展示出來,

349
00:30:07,000 --> 00:30:09,000
叫我們明白祂。

350
00:30:09,000 --> 00:30:12,000
His power is made strong in our weaknesses.

351
00:30:12,000 --> 00:30:18,000
祂的能力在我們軟弱的人的生命裡顯得明顯。

352
00:30:18,000 --> 00:30:22,000
The fourth good news is we can discover God's purpose in the wilderness.

353
00:30:22,000 --> 00:30:27,000
在曠野裡,第四個好消息就是我們可以去發現上帝的目的。

354
00:30:27,000 --> 00:30:34,000
Because God often uses the seasons of wilderness to teach us lessons which we otherwise cannot learn.

355
00:30:34,000 --> 00:30:42,000
原來上帝是要在曠野裡教我們,在其他環境裡我們學不到的功課。

356
00:30:42,000 --> 00:30:46,000
And these are the lessons that develop us as a people of faith.

357
00:30:46,000 --> 00:30:51,000
就是去發展我們成為一個有信念的子民的功課。

358
00:30:51,000 --> 00:30:55,000
Oh, but Satan attacks with his lies.

359
00:30:55,000 --> 00:31:01,000
不過,上帝的仇敵撒旦就是用謊言來攻擊我們。

360
00:31:01,000 --> 00:31:06,000
And one of the lies Satan tells us is there is no way out of your wilderness.

361
00:31:06,000 --> 00:31:13,000
其中一個謊言就是撒旦會告訴我們,你沒有領走,走不出這個曠野。

362
00:31:13,000 --> 00:31:20,000
We look at the problems, it becomes overwhelmingly big and we felt we cannot overcome the problem.

363
00:31:20,000 --> 00:31:30,000
當我們面對這個曠野,這個困難的時候,我們就感覺到實在是太山壓頂,我們沒有辦法可以勝過的。

364
00:31:30,000 --> 00:31:32,000
So we lose hope, we lose faith.

365
00:31:32,000 --> 00:31:35,000
我們沒有了盼望,所以沒有了信心。

366
00:31:35,000 --> 00:31:40,000
But yet God tells us, don't worry, you will find grace even in the wilderness.

367
00:31:40,000 --> 00:31:48,000
但是上帝告訴我們,不用擔心,雖然在曠野裏面,你都會得著恩典。

368
00:31:48,000 --> 00:31:55,000
That's what the prophet Jeremiah says in Jeremiah 31 verse 2, you will find grace in the wilderness.

369
00:31:55,000 --> 00:32:03,000
耶利米書,耶利米先知在31章裏面,他告訴我們,你會在曠野裏面找到恩寵。

370
00:32:03,000 --> 00:32:07,000
In other words, believe that God will bring you through the wilderness.

371
00:32:07,000 --> 00:32:10,000
就是相信上帝會帶你經過這個曠野。

372
00:32:10,000 --> 00:32:18,000
How then do we respond when we find ourselves in a season of wilderness, of difficult circumstances?

373
00:32:18,000 --> 00:32:25,000
當我們發現我們就是進入一個很困難,黑漆漆的一個處境的時候,我們可以怎樣回應上帝呢?

374
00:32:25,000 --> 00:32:31,000
The first thing is to realize everyone encounters a wilderness season of life.

375
00:32:31,000 --> 00:32:39,000
第一樣東西我們要去了解,去明白的就是,原來每一個人都會有這個曠野時刻。

376
00:32:39,000 --> 00:32:48,000
Some Christians wrongly think, if I am spiritual, if I walk in the center of God's will, I will never experience any difficulty or wilderness.

377
00:32:48,000 --> 00:32:59,000
有很多人就以為,錯誤地以為,我要虔誠,如果我是虔誠地去信,我就不會有這樣的曠野時刻出現了。

378
00:32:59,000 --> 00:33:04,000
That is untrue, because even Jesus was led by the Spirit into the wilderness.

379
00:33:04,000 --> 00:33:10,000
因為這個是錯誤的,耶穌都是被聖靈引導去進入曠野。

380
00:33:10,000 --> 00:33:15,000
We just learned that God allows this season to build us up.

381
00:33:15,000 --> 00:33:23,000
我們剛剛才學到,上帝容許曠野來進入我們的生命,為著我們得到建立。

382
00:33:23,000 --> 00:33:30,000
The second response is to realize that the greatest snake in the wilderness is our murmuring and complaining.

383
00:33:30,000 --> 00:33:47,000
第二樣東西我們要去了解,去明白的就是,這個在曠野裏面最大的陷阱就是,我們生命裏面,我們內心那些的暗沉,投訴,埋怨,那些東西。

384
00:33:47,000 --> 00:33:53,000
Many Christians in the wilderness complain and grumble because of unbelief.

385
00:33:53,000 --> 00:34:00,000
很多人在曠野裏面,他們生命的曠野裏面,就有很多的投訴,很多的不滿,因為他們不相信。

386
00:34:00,000 --> 00:34:05,000
What is the opposite of the spirit of complaining?

387
00:34:05,000 --> 00:34:09,000
埋怨投訴的相反是什麼呢?

388
00:34:09,000 --> 00:34:10,000
It's the spirit of gratitude.

389
00:34:10,000 --> 00:34:12,000
就是感激。

390
00:34:12,000 --> 00:34:14,000
I tell you what I found helpful.

391
00:34:14,000 --> 00:34:17,000
我告訴大家幫到我的是什麼?

392
00:34:17,000 --> 00:34:19,000
I keep a journal of gratitude.

393
00:34:19,000 --> 00:34:24,000
我就是寫一個感激清單,一個這樣的日記。

394
00:34:24,000 --> 00:34:32,000
And in that gratitude journal, I list down all the things I am grateful for, in spite of the circumstances.

395
00:34:32,000 --> 00:34:43,000
我就是清楚地記錄每一件事,我體會到,是令到我感激的那些事情,雖然那個環境都是很惡劣。

396
00:34:43,000 --> 00:34:46,000
About two years ago, I was diagnosed with brain tumor.

397
00:34:46,000 --> 00:34:49,000
兩年前,我確診了我腦裏面有個腫瘤。

398
00:34:49,000 --> 00:34:57,000
I still have a tumor in my brain right now, because the surgeon says I rather not operate it and take it out.

399
00:34:57,000 --> 00:35:07,000
我現在仍然有個腫瘤,因為醫生說我不需要做這個手術,所以我仍然容許這個腫瘤在那裏。

400
00:35:07,000 --> 00:35:13,000
And the reason why he says I don't recommend the operation is because there will be risks.

401
00:35:13,000 --> 00:35:17,000
他不建議我做手術,因為有風險。

402
00:35:17,000 --> 00:35:26,000
And he tells me with this, it is a benign tumor, and you can still therefore travel and administer, it is all right.

403
00:35:26,000 --> 00:35:36,000
這個腫瘤都是良性的,但你現在仍然都可以周遊列國去做服事,所以你不需要做這個手術。

404
00:35:36,000 --> 00:35:40,000
He just said come every year, do an MRI, and we monitor it.

405
00:35:40,000 --> 00:35:46,000
每年來做一個檢查,然後你就可以繼續生活了。

406
00:35:46,000 --> 00:35:52,000
So in my gratitude journal, I give thanks to God, in spite of the circumstance, His wonderful blessing.

407
00:35:52,000 --> 00:36:01,000
我就在我的日記裏面寫下,上帝這樣恩待我,雖然這個都是帶來一些困難。

408
00:36:01,000 --> 00:36:10,000
But my neurosurgeon says in any case, if you have a severe headache or you are having a fainting, you must go to the hospital immediately.

409
00:36:10,000 --> 00:36:18,000
雖然是這樣,但如果你發現你自己是很頭痛,甚至你暈的時候,你要立刻去醫院。

410
00:36:18,000 --> 00:36:25,000
My answer is simple, my looking is straight to God, because my Father knows what is best.

411
00:36:25,000 --> 00:36:31,000
我的答案很簡單,我的天父在看著我,他知道什麼是最好的。

412
00:36:31,000 --> 00:36:37,000
I can choose either to complain, God, I am a servant, I am serving you, how come I have all these medical problems?

413
00:36:37,000 --> 00:36:43,000
我可以投訴,可以埋怨,上帝,我是服侍你的,我是你的僕人,為什麼會這樣?

414
00:36:43,000 --> 00:36:49,000
Or I can give thanks and say, wow, in spite of all these problems, God can still use me.

415
00:36:49,000 --> 00:36:55,000
我亦都可以感謝,雖然是這樣,我仍然是蒙上帝去使用。

416
00:36:55,000 --> 00:36:58,000
Learn to walk by gratitude.

417
00:36:58,000 --> 00:37:05,000
我們要學在生活裏面,學成為一個有感激的人。

418
00:37:05,000 --> 00:37:09,000
The third response is to realize we have a choice in the wilderness.

419
00:37:09,000 --> 00:37:14,000
第三樣我們要學習,原來在曠野裏面,我們真的可以選擇。

420
00:37:14,000 --> 00:37:20,000
The important choice in Isaiah 40 verse 3, in the wilderness, prepare the way of the Lord.

421
00:37:20,000 --> 00:37:29,000
這個在二賽書第四十章裏面所講的是一個很重要的選擇,就是在曠野裏面預備耶和華的道路。

422
00:37:29,000 --> 00:37:35,000
Either we walk in unbelief and worries, or we walk by faith and restedness. It is a choice.

423
00:37:35,000 --> 00:37:44,000
我們可以在這個曠野裏面,因為各樣的焦慮,懷疑,我們就進入這個困難。

424
00:37:44,000 --> 00:37:49,000
或者是用信心,放鬆的去讚美我們的主。

425
00:37:49,000 --> 00:37:53,000
So in the wilderness, I am not just looking for God's blessing to me.

426
00:37:53,000 --> 00:38:00,000
我在曠野裏面,我並不只是在等上帝怎樣去祝福我。

427
00:38:00,000 --> 00:38:04,000
I am not just looking for God's blessing through me in my ministry.

428
00:38:04,000 --> 00:38:09,000
我並不只是在等上帝怎樣使用我,透過我去祝福別人。

429
00:38:09,000 --> 00:38:13,000
Most importantly, I am looking for God's work in me.

430
00:38:13,000 --> 00:38:22,000
我最著緊的就是,在曠野裏面,我在看上帝要怎樣在我生命裏面做功夫。

431
00:38:22,000 --> 00:38:25,000
To draw me in a deeper relationship with Him.

432
00:38:25,000 --> 00:38:28,000
引導我進入一個更深的親密。

433
00:38:28,000 --> 00:38:32,000
And the fourth response is to heed the prophetic voice of God in the scriptures.

434
00:38:32,000 --> 00:38:39,000
第四個回應,就是我們要在聖經中留意上帝的聲音。

435
00:38:39,000 --> 00:38:43,000
Listen to what the prophetic voice says in Isaiah chapter 4 verse 6 onwards.

436
00:38:43,000 --> 00:38:49,000
請大家留意二賽書四十章第六節以後,先知要講的說話。

437
00:38:49,000 --> 00:38:53,000
A voice says, "Cry." And the prophet asked, "I said, 'What shall I cry?'"

438
00:38:53,000 --> 00:38:58,000
聲音說, "你喊吧。我說,我喊什麼呢?"

439
00:38:58,000 --> 00:39:06,000
And this is what it seems to say, "Cry that all flesh is grass, and all is beauty is like the flower of the field."

440
00:39:06,000 --> 00:39:16,000
你驟眼來去看,就好像你叫什麼?叫血肉之軀都是如草啊,好像野地的花。

441
00:39:16,000 --> 00:39:21,000
verse 8, "Cry out that the grass withers, the flower fades, but the word of God stands forever."

442
00:39:21,000 --> 00:39:28,000
好像第八節這樣說,草彼枯乾,花彼雕著,唯有以我們的神的話,永遠立定。

443
00:39:28,000 --> 00:39:34,000
So listen to what this passage says. There is a spirit of the voice of the spirit says, "Cry."

444
00:39:34,000 --> 00:39:36,000
The prophet says, "What shall I cry?"

445
00:39:36,000 --> 00:39:43,000
留意這一段的聖經,聖靈就說,你呼喊吧,先知就說,那呼喊什麼呢?

446
00:39:43,000 --> 00:39:49,000
And the word of the Lord is, "Everything is transitory, not permanent except the word of God."

447
00:39:49,000 --> 00:39:55,000
聖經就說,所有的東西都是暫時的,除了上帝的說話。

448
00:39:55,000 --> 00:39:58,000
But that's not what Isaiah was supposed to cry out.

449
00:39:58,000 --> 00:40:03,000
其實先知不是要呼叫這些的。

450
00:40:03,000 --> 00:40:08,000
Rather, that's the reason why he should cry out what he was told to cry out.

451
00:40:08,000 --> 00:40:13,000
有一個原因是令到他要去呼喊某一樣東西。

452
00:40:13,000 --> 00:40:15,000
What shall I cry out? Isaiah asked.

453
00:40:15,000 --> 00:40:19,000
Yu Tsui Hsiang在問,我要呼喊些什麼?

454
00:40:19,000 --> 00:40:23,000
And the answer is, there is nothing worthy to be cried out because everything is temporary.

455
00:40:23,000 --> 00:40:27,000
The only thing worthy is the word of God that is eternal.

456
00:40:27,000 --> 00:40:33,000
上帝的說話就是說,其實沒有什麼東西是值得你們去呼喊的。

457
00:40:33,000 --> 00:40:36,000
除了上帝的說話,唯有上帝的說話是永存。

458
00:40:36,000 --> 00:40:39,000
So in the wilderness, what are we to cry out?

459
00:40:39,000 --> 00:40:41,000
在曠野裏面,我們要呼喊些什麼呢?

460
00:40:41,000 --> 00:40:45,000
In the wilderness, what's the word of God that will encourage us?

461
00:40:45,000 --> 00:40:50,000
在曠野裏面,有什麼神的說話是可以鼓勵我們呢?

462
00:40:50,000 --> 00:40:52,000
Isaiah 40 verse 9 gives the answer.

463
00:40:52,000 --> 00:40:55,000
二孩書四十章九節給我們答案。

464
00:40:55,000 --> 00:40:59,000
Go on up a high mountain, O Zion, herald of good news.

465
00:40:59,000 --> 00:41:03,000
Live up your voice with strength, O Jerusalem, herald of good news.

466
00:41:03,000 --> 00:41:08,000
Live it up, fear not. Say to the cities of Judah, Behold your God.

467
00:41:08,000 --> 00:41:13,000
第九節說,報好信息的錫安,要在登高山,報好信息的耶路撒冷。

468
00:41:13,000 --> 00:41:18,000
要極力揚聲,不要懼怕。對猶大的城鎮說,看呀,你們的神。

469
00:41:18,000 --> 00:41:23,000
That's what the word of God proclaim, in your wilderness, behold your God.

470
00:41:23,000 --> 00:41:29,000
在曠野裏面,你們要呼喊的就是,看呀,你們的神。

471
00:41:29,000 --> 00:41:34,000
In your wilderness, live up your eyes to God, because God is mightily at work in your life.

472
00:41:34,000 --> 00:41:40,000
在你的曠野裏面,你要仰望你的神,去看上這個偉大的神,

473
00:41:40,000 --> 00:41:42,000
在你的生命裏面要做些什麼?

474
00:41:42,000 --> 00:41:48,000
In your wilderness, don't walk with your own wisdom, walk with the wisdom of God's word.

475
00:41:48,000 --> 00:41:55,000
在你的曠野裏面,不要用你的智慧來去生活,用上帝的說話,叫你看到上帝的工作。

476
00:41:55,000 --> 00:41:57,000
Look up and prepare the way for the Lord.

477
00:41:57,000 --> 00:42:00,000
所以仰望去預備上帝的道路。

478
00:42:00,000 --> 00:42:01,000
Behold your God.

479
00:42:01,000 --> 00:42:04,000
看呀,你們的神。

480
00:42:04,000 --> 00:42:05,000
I want to close with a true story.

481
00:42:05,000 --> 00:42:08,000
我用一個真的故事來結束。

482
00:42:08,000 --> 00:42:11,000
It is about a chess expert by the name of Paul Morphy.

483
00:42:11,000 --> 00:42:17,000
有一個象棋大師的名字叫做Paul Morphy。

484
00:42:17,000 --> 00:42:20,000
He was invited to dinner in a large house.

485
00:42:20,000 --> 00:42:24,000
有一個人邀請他去到一個大屋裏面做晚餐。

486
00:42:24,000 --> 00:42:28,000
And in the house he saw a painting of two chess players.

487
00:42:28,000 --> 00:42:35,000
在這個餐廳裏面,他看到一幅畫有兩個人物正在對弈。

488
00:42:35,000 --> 00:42:41,000
It was a painting of a young man playing chess with Satan, and Satan has won, and the young man looks hopeless.

489
00:42:41,000 --> 00:42:47,000
這幅畫的兩個人物,一個是年輕人,另一個是撒旦,他們正在對弈。

490
00:42:47,000 --> 00:42:54,000
而那個情況是撒旦在贏,差不多贏了,這個年輕人已經很絕望。

491
00:42:54,000 --> 00:42:57,000
And the name of the painting is Checkmate.

492
00:42:57,000 --> 00:43:02,000
而這個畫的題目就是將軍死了。

493
00:43:02,000 --> 00:43:04,000
In other words, it is game over.

494
00:43:04,000 --> 00:43:06,000
就是玩完了。

495
00:43:06,000 --> 00:43:12,000
But the chess expert Paul Morphy says, you know, I can take the young man's position and win against Satan.

496
00:43:12,000 --> 00:43:20,000
Paul Morphy就對那個家主說,如果我來代這個年輕人的話,我有把握去贏到撒旦的。

497
00:43:20,000 --> 00:43:30,000
His host said, Oh, Mr. Morphy, not even you can turn the chess game around.

498
00:43:30,000 --> 00:43:36,000
Paul Morphy says, why don't we try and see? So they set up the chess pieces according to the painting.

499
00:43:36,000 --> 00:43:50,000
And he played the game, and to the surprise of everyone, he actually won the game and turned it around.

500
00:43:50,000 --> 00:44:09,000
In fact, it is such a surprising twist around that its Chronicle in the Chess Chronicles published in New York in August 1888.

501
00:44:09,000 --> 00:44:24,000
這個局的棋是十分經典,經典到在1818年的這個棋的雜誌裡面刊登了出來。

502
00:44:24,000 --> 00:44:26,000
It stunned the chess world.

503
00:44:26,000 --> 00:44:29,000
整個的象棋世界震驚。

504
00:44:29,000 --> 00:44:33,000
So his friend asked him, how did you know the chess game can be turned around?

505
00:44:33,000 --> 00:44:38,000
那個家主就在問,你怎樣知道這個局棋是可以逆轉的呢?

506
00:44:38,000 --> 00:44:41,000
He said, when I examined the painting, I made a discovery.

507
00:44:41,000 --> 00:44:48,000
Paul Morphy就說,當我去檢查這個棋盤的時候,我就發現了一些東西。

508
00:44:48,000 --> 00:44:54,000
I discovered it's not a checkmate, not game over, because the king has one more move.

509
00:44:54,000 --> 00:45:02,000
我就發現是未死得的,因為這個棋的皇帝的棋子還有一步可以走的。

510
00:45:02,000 --> 00:45:06,000
And when the king makes the move, the entire chess game changed.

511
00:45:06,000 --> 00:45:12,000
而這個皇帝走過一步的時候,整個的局勢就會變了。

512
00:45:12,000 --> 00:45:16,000
When our king, the Lord Jesus, was crucified, Satan thought he has won.

513
00:45:16,000 --> 00:45:23,000
當我們的君王耶穌在十字架上面被釘死的時候,撒旦就認為他贏了。

514
00:45:23,000 --> 00:45:26,000
But the Lord Jesus has one more move. He rose from the dead.

515
00:45:26,000 --> 00:45:30,000
但是我們的君王還有一步走,就是他從死裡復活。

516
00:45:30,000 --> 00:45:32,000
And everything was changed around.

517
00:45:32,000 --> 00:45:33,000
一切都變了。

518
00:45:33,000 --> 00:45:38,000
No matter how difficult your circumstance is, our king has one more move.

519
00:45:38,000 --> 00:45:43,000
無論你的環境是多麼的惡劣,我們的君王還有一步走。

520
00:45:43,000 --> 00:45:46,000
Prepare your heart in the wilderness.

521
00:45:46,000 --> 00:45:49,000
在你們的曠野裡,預備你們的心。

522
00:45:49,000 --> 00:45:51,000
Behold your God.

523
00:45:51,000 --> 00:45:54,000
仰望看你們的神。

524
00:45:54,000 --> 00:45:56,000
Prepare the way for the Lord.

525
00:45:56,000 --> 00:45:59,000
預備耶和華你們的神的道路。

526
00:45:59,000 --> 00:46:03,000
Because our king has one more move.

527
00:46:03,000 --> 00:46:05,000
因為我們的君王還有一步走。

528
00:46:05,000 --> 00:46:06,000
Will you bow with me and pray?

529
00:46:06,000 --> 00:46:07,000
我們一起祈禱。

530
00:46:07,000 --> 00:46:11,000
Holy Father, thank you for the victory that is in King Jesus.

531
00:46:11,000 --> 00:46:15,000
天父啊,我們為耶穌基督的勝利感謝你。

532
00:46:15,000 --> 00:46:18,000
In our wilderness, draw us to Him.

533
00:46:18,000 --> 00:46:22,000
在我們的曠野裡,吸引我們去親近主。

534
00:46:22,000 --> 00:46:25,000
To behold the way of the Lord.

535
00:46:25,000 --> 00:46:29,000
去仰望我們的主。

536
00:46:29,000 --> 00:46:32,000
To behold the power of God.

537
00:46:32,000 --> 00:46:35,000
去仰望我們上帝的能力。

538
00:46:35,000 --> 00:46:39,000
To keep on walking in faith and not in doubt.

539
00:46:39,000 --> 00:46:42,000
繼續用信心,而不是用懷疑去走下去。

540
00:46:42,000 --> 00:46:45,000
To prepare the way of the Lord in the wilderness.

541
00:46:45,000 --> 00:46:48,000
去在曠野裡預備我們上帝的道路。

542
00:46:48,000 --> 00:46:50,000
We thank you in Jesus' name.

543
00:46:50,000 --> 00:46:52,000
我們感謝主奉耶穌的名。

